/src/ittf/examples/codegen/jsmodel/jsnode.js.ittf

                        


   1 module
   2     kind jsfile
   3     var _ = require('lodash')
   4     $include jsnode/keywords
   5     $include jsnode/attributes
   6     class JsNode
   7         ctor
   8             param element
   9             param name
  10             set this.wzElement = checkKeyword(element)
  11             set this.wzName = name || ''
  12             set this.statements = []
  13             set this.wzParent = null
  14             set this.paramNames = []
  15             set this.constrainedParams = []
  16         m addStatement
  17             param element
  18             param name
  19             # log 'addStatement', element, name, checkKeyword(element)
  20             if element === 'param'
  21                 _ this.paramNames.push(name)
  22             elif isAttribute(this.wzElement + '/' + checkKeyword(element))
  23                 set this[checkKeyword(element)] = name
  24                 return this
  25             else
  26                 var s = new JsNode(element, name)
  27                 set s.wzParent = this
  28                 _ this.statements.push(s)
  29                 return s
  30         m getParams
  31             if !this.params
  32                 set this.params = []
  33                 set this.paramNames = []
  34                 var stms = []
  35                 foreach item in this.statements
  36                     if item.wzElement == 'param'
  37                         # log 'param', item.wzName
  38                         _ this.params.push(item.wzName)
  39                         _ this.paramNames.push(item.wzName)
  40                     else
  41                         _ stms.push(item)
  42                 set this.statements = stms
  43             return this.params
  44         m findCtor
  45             return
  46                 _ _.find
  47                     @ this.statements
  48                     function
  49                         param item
  50                         return item.wzElement === 'ctor'
  51         m getBaseArgs
  52             param name
  53             if !this.bases
  54                 set this.bases = []
  55                 var stms = []
  56                 foreach item in this.statements
  57                     if item.wzElement == 'base'
  58                         # log 'base', item.wzName
  59                         _ this.bases.push(item)
  60                     else
  61                         _ stms.push(item)
  62                 set this.statements = stms
  63             var found = null
  64             _ this.bases.forEach
  65                 function
  66                     param item
  67                     set found = found || (item.wzName === name ? item : null)
  68                     return found
  69         m loadFromMTree
  70             param mTree
  71             +
  72             if mTree.nodes.length != 1
  73                 throw new Error('JsNode.loadFromMTree error: mTree.nodes.length must be == 1')
  74             var n = mTree.nodes[0]
  75             set this.wzElement = checkKeyword(n.n)
  76             set this.wzName = checkKeyword(n.v)
  77             +
  78             foreach item in n.children
  79                 _ statement(this, item)
  80             +
  81             function statement
  82                 param jsnode
  83                 param node
  84                 var c_jsnode
  85                     _ jsnode.addStatement
  86                         @ node.n
  87                         @ node.v
  88                 foreach item in node.children
  89                     _ statement(c_jsnode, item)
  90     set module.exports = JsNode

   1 loader( call)

  17     stm( memberCall)

  62     function requireParents
  63         param candidate
  64         var ancestor = candidate.parent
  65         while ancestor
  66             if !ancestor.isRequired
  67                 _ ancestor.constraints.push
  68                     {
  69                         @ constraintType 'required'
  70                         @ paramName ancestor.prm.wzName
  71                         @ paramType prmTypeFromElement(ancestor.prm.wzElement)
  72                         @ accessPath ancestor.accessPath
  73                 set ancestor.isRequired = true
  74             set ancestor = ancestor.parent
  75     function prmTypeFromElement
  76         param wzElement
  77         if wzElement === 'stringParam'
  78             return 'string'
  79         elif wzElement === 'numberParam'
  80             return 'number'
  81         elif wzElement === 'booleanParam'
  82             return 'boolean'
  83         elif wzElement === 'anyParam'
  84             return 'any'
  85         elif wzElement === 'functionParam'
  86             return 'function'
  87         elif wzElement === 'objectParam'
  88             return 'object'
  89         elif wzElement === 'arrayParam'
  90             return 'array'
  91         elif wzElement === 'arrayOrObjectParam'
  92             return 'arrayOrObject'
  93         elif wzElement === 'callbackParam'
  94             return 'callback'
  95         elif wzElement === 'optionsCallbackParam'
  96             return 'optionsCallback'

                    

                

                

                    

                        
/src/ittf/lib/artifacts/js/module/gen/codegen/util/t/lineparser/_old_parseNameValueRaw.js.ittf

                        


   1 $group
   2     #
   3         # name = first not (blank or tab) char sequence
   4         # value = all remaining chars after name + (blank or tab)
   5         # ignore quotes unless the value part is enclosed with double quotes : "
   6         # example (with no quotes)
   7         # trip 'to the london bridge'
   8         # name() = trip
   9         # value() = 'to the london bridge'
  10         # example (quotes ignored 1)
  11         # trip 'to the ' + city + ' bridge'
  12         # name() = trip
  13         # value() = 'to the ' + city + ' bridge'
  14         # example (quotes escaped)
  15         # trip "to the " + city + " bridge"
  16         # name() = trip
  17         # value() = "to the \" + city + \" bridge"
  18     set md.parseNameValueRaw
  19         function
  20             param text
  21             param node
  22             var
  23                 decl name = ''
  24                 decl value = []
  25                 decl quotes = []
  26             if verify.isNotEmpty(text)
  27                 var
  28                     decl ch
  29                     decl state = 0
  30                     decl l = text.length
  31                 for var i = 0; i < l; i++
  32                     set ch = text[i]
  33                     if state == 2 && (ch == '"' || ch == "'") && text[i-1] !== '\\'
  34                         _ quotes.push({ q: ch, p: value.length })
  35                     if ch == ' ' || ch == '\t'
  36                         if state == 0
  37                             + ;
  38                         elif state == 1
  39                             set state = 2
  40                         elif state == 2
  41                             _ value.push(ch)
  42                     else
  43                         if state == 0
  44                             set name = ch
  45                             set state = 1
  46                         elif state == 1
  47                             set name += ch
  48                         elif state == 2
  49                             _ value.push(ch)
  50             return
  51                 {
  52                     @ name
  53                         function
  54                             return name
  55                     @ value
  56                         function
  57                             if quotes.length > 0
  58                                 # log '*=*=*= temporary wizzi-codegen.lineparser. quotes, value: ', quotes, value.join('')
  59                                 # log quotes[0].q, quotes[quotes.length -1].q
  60                             if quotes.length > 2 && quotes[0].q === quotes[quotes.length -1].q && quotes[0].q === '"'
  61                                 var q = quotes[0].q
  62                                 for var i = 1; i < quotes.length -1; i ++
  63                                     if quotes[i].q === q
  64                                         set value[quotes[i].p] = '\\' + q
  65                                 # log '*=*=*= temporary wizzi-codegen.lineparser. value: ', value.join('')
  66                             return value.join('')
  67                     @ hasValue
  68                         function
  69                             return value.length > 0

   1 $group
   2     set md.parse

   4             param text

   9                 return
  10                     {
  11                         @ tokens

  13                         @ join

  15                                 return ''

  27                         @ text ''

  33                     elif state === 1

  58                             {

  65                         set state = 0

  67                         set token.text += closeMacro

  69                     set token.text += ch
  70             if state === 1
  71                 set token.text += openMacro
  72                 set state = 0
  73             elif state === 11
  74                 set token.text += closeMacro
  75                 set state = 2
  76             if token.text.length > 0

/src/ittf/lib/artifacts/js/module/gen/codegen/util/t/lineparser/parseNameValueRaw.js.ittf

                        


   1 $group
   2     var STATE_WAIT_NAME = 0
   3     var STATE_NAME = 1
   4     var STATE_WAIT_VALUE = 2
   5     var STATE_VALUE = 3
   6     var STATE_ENDED = 4
   7     var STATE_NAME_BRACKET = 5
   8     set md.parseNameValueRaw
   9         function
  10             param text
  11             param node
  12             param options
  13             set options = options || {}
  14             var isObjectProperty = options.objectProperty
  15             var name_buf = []
  16             var value_buf = []
  17             if verify.isNotEmpty(text)
  18                 var
  19                     decl ch
  20                     decl l = text.length
  21                     decl state = 0
  22                     decl q = null
  23                     decl bracketLevel = 0
  24                 for var i = 0; i < l; i++
  25                     set ch = text[i]
  26                     if state == STATE_NAME_BRACKET
  27                         _ name_buf.push(ch)
  28                         if ch == ']'
  29                             set bracketLevel--
  30                             if bracketLevel == 0
  31                                 set state = STATE_WAIT_VALUE
  32                         elif ch == '['
  33                             set bracketLevel++
  34                     elif isObjectProperty && state == STATE_WAIT_NAME && ch == '['
  35                         _ name_buf.push(ch)
  36                         set state = STATE_NAME_BRACKET
  37                         set bracketLevel++
  38                     elif q != null
  39                         # state MUST BE STATE_NAME or STATE_VALUE
  40                         if state === STATE_NAME
  41                             _ name_buf.push(ch)
  42                         elif state === STATE_VALUE
  43                             _ value_buf.push(ch)
  44                         else
  45                             # this is a bug
  46                             throw new Error('BUG. parseNameValue invalid state ' + state)
  47                         if ch == '\\'
  48                             set i++
  49                             set ch = text[i]
  50                             if state === STATE_NAME
  51                                 _ name_buf.push(ch)
  52                             elif state === STATE_VALUE
  53                                 _ value_buf.push(ch)
  54                         elif ch == q
  55                             set q = null
  56                             if state === STATE_NAME
  57                                 set state = STATE_WAIT_VALUE
  58                     elif ch == '"' || ch == '\''
  59                         # state MUST BE STATE_WAIT_NAME or STATE_WAIT_VALUE
  60                         if state === STATE_NAME
  61                             throw new errors.NodeError("parseNameValue error. Invalid use of quote inside a name part. Source: " + text, node)
  62                         elif state === STATE_VALUE
  63                             _ value_buf.push(ch)
  64                         elif state === STATE_ENDED
  65                             throw new errors.NodeError("parseNameValue error. Invalid quote found after value. Source: " + text, node)
  66                         elif state === STATE_WAIT_NAME
  67                             set state = STATE_NAME
  68                             _ name_buf.push(ch)
  69                             set q = ch
  70                         elif state === STATE_WAIT_VALUE
  71                             set state = STATE_VALUE
  72                             _ value_buf.push(ch)
  73                             set q = ch
  74                     elif ch == ' ' || ch == '\t'
  75                         if state === STATE_NAME
  76                             set state = STATE_WAIT_VALUE
  77                         elif state === STATE_VALUE
  78                             _ value_buf.push(ch)
  79                         else
  80                             # ok. no action.
  81                     elif ch == '\r' || ch == '\n'
  82                         throw new errors.NodeError("parseNameValue error. Invalid char. Line cannot contain line breaks. Source: " + text, node)
  83                     else
  84                         if state === STATE_WAIT_NAME
  85                             set state = STATE_NAME
  86                             _ name_buf.push(ch)
  87                         elif state === STATE_WAIT_VALUE
  88                             set state = STATE_VALUE
  89                             _ value_buf.push(ch)
  90                         elif state === STATE_NAME
  91                             _ name_buf.push(ch)
  92                         elif state === STATE_VALUE
  93                             _ value_buf.push(ch)
  94                         elif state === STATE_ENDED
  95                             throw new errors.NodeError("parseNameValue error. Invalid char after value. Source: " + text, node)
  96             if q !== null && state === STATE_NAME
  97                 # This almost surely is an error, but we cannot judge.
  98             return
  99                 {
 100                     @ name
 101                         function
 102                             return name_buf.join('')
 103                     @ value
 104                         function
 105                             return value_buf.join('')
 106                     @ hasValue
 107                         function
 108                             return value_buf.length > 0

/src/ittf/lib/wizzi/schemas/t/js/classes.wfschema.ittf

                        


   1 $group
   2     e class : statement
   3         # A javascript class
   4         a super
   5         a extends
   6         m findCtor
   7             return _.find(this.statements, function(item) { return item.wzElement === 'ctor' })
   8         m wzInitialize
   9             set ctx.modelState = ctx.modelState || {}
  10             # log 'wizzi-js.model.class.modelState', ctx.modelState
  11             set ctx.modelState.hasClasses = true
  12             if this.extends && this.extends.length > 0
  13                 set this.super = this.extends
  14             else
  15                 var tokens = this.wzName.split(':')
  16                 if tokens.length == 2
  17                     set this.wzName = tokens[0]
  18                     set this.super = tokens[1]
  19         #
  20         # ittf
  21         # class Horse
  22         # super Animal
  23         # ctor
  24         # string name
  25         # required
  26         # { options
  27         # boolean canSpeakLikeAHuman
  28         # required
  29         # set this.name = name
  30         # set this.options = options
  31         # m sayHello
  32         # if this.options.canSpeakLikeAHuman
  33         # log 'Hello i am ' + this.name
  34         # else
  35         # log 'Hii i am ' + this.name
  36         #
  37     e ctor : function
  38         r base/s
  39         m getBaseArgs
  40             var ret = []
  41             foreach item in this.bases
  42                 _ ret.push(item.wzName)
  43             return ret
  44         #
  45         # ittf
  46         # class Horse
  47         # super Animal
  48         # ctor
  49         # string name
  50         # base name
  51         #
  52     e base : statement
  53         #
  54         # ittf
  55         # see 'ctor' elementg example
  56     e method : function
  57         tag m
  58         a_flag( static )
  59         a_flag( async )
  60         # ittf
  61         # class Foo
  62         # m sayHello
  63         # string name
  64         # log 'Hello ' + name
  65     e property : function
  66         a_flag( static )
  67         # ittf
  68         # class Foo
  69         # property options
  70     e new : statement
  71         # ittf:
  72         # var h
  73         # new Hello
  74         # var j
  75         # new Hello
  76         # function
  77         # param p
  78         # + ...
  79         # js:
  80         # var h = new Hello();
  81         # var j = new Hello(function(p) { ... });
  82     e type : statement
  83         # used by the 'new' element
  84         # see wizzi-codegen.js.statements.var
  85         # TODO example
  86         # FIXME Cannot find examples and the reason for this element
  87         #

/src/ittf/lib/wizzi/schemas/t/js/functions.wfschema.ittf

                        


   1 $group
   2     e function : statement
   3         r param/s
   4         m wzinitialize
   5             set this.paramNames = []
   6             set this.constrainedParams = []
   7             set this.hasCallbackParam = false
   8             set this.hasOptionsCallbackParam = false
   9             foreach item in this.params
  10                 if item.wzElement === 'callbackParam'
  11                     _ this.paramNames.push('callback')
  12                     set this.hasCallbackParam = true
  13                 elif item.wzElement === 'optionsCallbackParam'
  14                     _ this.paramNames.push('options')
  15                     _ this.paramNames.push('callback')
  16                     set this.hasOptionsCallbackParam = true
  17                 else
  18                     if item.textified && item.textified.length > 0
  19                         _ this.paramNames.push(item.textified)
  20                     else
  21                         _ this.paramNames.push(item.wzName)
  22                 _ this.constrainedParams.push(item)
  23         #
  24         # ittf
  25         # function sum
  26         # param a
  27         # param a
  28         # return a + b
  29         #
  30     e iife : function
  31         a unary-prefix
  32         # ittf
  33         # iife
  34         # unary-prefix ;
  35         # param x
  36         # param y
  37         # return alpha = x + ': ' + y
  38         # (
  39         # @ key
  40         # @ id
  41         # js
  42         # ;(function(x, y) {
  43         # return alpha = x + ': ' + y;
  44         # })(key, id)
  45         #
  46     e arrowfunction : function
  47         tag =>
  48         # es6 feature
  49         #
  50         # ittf
  51         # var handler
  52         # =>
  53         # param event
  54         #
  55     e generatorfunction : function
  56         tag function*
  57         # es6 feature
  58         # reference https://developer.mozilla.org/it/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Operators/yield
  59         # ittf
  60         # function* foo
  61         # var index = 0
  62         # while index <= 2
  63         # yield index++
  64         #
  65     e yield : statement
  66         # es6 feature
  67         # reference https://developer.mozilla.org/it/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Operators/yield
  68         # ittf
  69         # function* foo
  70         # var index = 0
  71         # while index <= 2
  72         # yield index++
  73     e return : statement
  74         # Can return any object or function.
  75         #
  76         # ittf
  77         # return 0
  78         # return
  79         # {
  80         # @ result a + b
  81         #
  82         # return
  83         # _ Math.sum
  84         # @ a
  85         # @ b
  86         #
  87         # return
  88         # function
  89         # param a
  90         # param b
  91         # ...

   1 $group
   2     e jsObject : statement
   3         tag {
   4         # Declares an object structure.
   5         # ittf:
   6         # var user
   7         # {
   8         # @ name 'stefi'
   9         # @ birth 1957
  10         #
  11         # It can be used everywhere an object can be used
  12         # ittf
  13         # var user
  14         # _ db.getUser
  15         # {
  16         # @ name 'arthur'
  17         #
  18         m wzinitialize
  19             # a Dsl that uses this could be 'graphql'
  20             set this.isDslCall = false
  21             foreach item in this.statements
  22                 if item.wzElement === 'namedCallParam'
  23                     set this.isDslCall = true
  24     e get : statement
  25         tag get
  26         # es6 - Defines a getter on a new object in the object initializer
  27         # reference https://developer.mozilla.org/it/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Functions/get
  28         #
  29         # ittf
  30         # var obj
  31         # {
  32         # @ log ['test']
  33         # get latest
  34         # if this.log.length == 0
  35         # return undefined
  36         # return this.log[this.log.length - 1]
  37         #
  38     e jsArray : statement
  39         tag [
  40         # Declares an array structure.
  41         # ittf:
  42         # var users
  43         # [
  44         # {
  45         # @ name 'stefi'
  46         # @ birth 1957
  47         # {
  48         # @ name 'arthur'
  49         # @ birth 1955
  50         #
  51     e jsPropertyOrValue : statement
  52         tag @
  53         # This element is used in many contexts with a different semantic.
  54         #
  55         # As children of a 'jsObject' element it is an object property.
  56         # ittf
  57         # var user
  58         # {
  59         # @ name 'annie'
  60         #
  61         # As children of a 'call', 'memberCall', 'decoratorCall', 'callOnValue' element
  62         # is a function call argument.
  63         # ittf
  64         # var user
  65         # _ db.getUser
  66         # @ name 'annie'
  67         #
  68         # As a children of an element derived from the 'htmlelement' element
  69         # is an html element attribute.
  70         # ittf
  71         # m render
  72         # return
  73         # div
  74         # button Press me
  75         # @ onClick { this.handleClick() }
  76         #
  77         m wzinitialize
  78             # a Dsl that uses this could be 'graphql'
  79             set this.isDslCall = false
  80             foreach item in this.statements
  81                 if item.wzElement === 'namedCallParam'
  82                     set this.isDslCall = true
  83     e namedCallParam : statement
  84         tag :
  85         # graphql-query
  86         # { allMarkdownRemark
  87         # : sort
  88         # {
  89         # @ order DESC
  90         # @ fields
  91         # [
  92         # @ frontmatter___date
  93         # : limit 1000
  94     e jsonStatementTree : statement
  95         tag jst
  96         # Contains the stringified tree structure of a statement element.
  97         # Normally this element is generated and is usefull when the 'js' ittf document
  98         # is itself a generated artifact.
  99         #
 100         # The artifact generator will JSON.parse the wzName property
 101         # of this element and will obtain a 'statement' element to process.

   1 $group
   2     e require : statement
   3     e import : statement
   4         # reference http://2ality.com/2014/09/es6-modules-final.html
   5         a from
   6         a default
   7         a as
   8         m wzInitialize
   9             set this.specifiers = []
  10             foreach item in this.statements
  11                 if item.wzElement === 'jsPropertyOrValue'
  12                     _ this.specifiers.push(item)
  13     e set : statement
  14         #
  15         # The set element do not relate to any javascript synthax element but is
  16         # fundamental in the 'js' language schema.
  17         # A wizzi schema cannot have free node names (tags). User names
  18         # cannot be node names but always must be node values.
  19         # Whenever javascript has a left hand side item that is an user name
  20         # must be preceded by set.
  21         #
  22         # ittf
  23         # set user.name = 'stefi'
  24         # js
  25         # user.name = 'stefi';
  26         #
  27         # In a 'set' element the wzName is written as is. If it is a top statement
  28         # the semicolon is added.
  29         #
  30     e export : statement
  31         # reference http://2ality.com/2014/09/es6-modules-final.html
  32         # ittf
  33         # export var|let|const foo = Math.sqrt(2)
  34         # export
  35         # var|let|const foo = Math.sqrt(2)
  36         # export
  37         # var|let|const foo
  38         # {
  39         # @ name 'stefi'
  40         # export
  41         # function foo
  42         # param x
  43         # export default
  44         # function
  45         # { options
  46     e_tag( exportDefault,  export-default,  statement)
  47     e if : statement
  48         #
  49         # ittf:
  50         # if a === b
  51         # elif a === c
  52         # else
  53         # js:
  54         # if ( a === b ) {
  55         # }
  56         # else if ( a === c ) {
  57         # }
  58         # else {
  59         # }
  60         #
  61     e elif : statement
  62         # ittf
  63         # see 'if' element
  64     e else : statement
  65         # ittf
  66         # see 'if' element
  67     e for : statement
  68         # ittf
  69         # for var k in object3
  70         # log k, object3[k]
  71         #
  72     e foreach : statement
  73         # ittf
  74         # foreach item in arr5
  75         # log 'item ', i, item
  76         #
  77         # js
  78         # var i, i_len=arr5.length, item;
  79         # for (i=0; i<i_len; i++) {
  80         # item = arr5[i];
  81         # console.log('item ', i, item);
  82         # }
  83         #
  84     e backeach : statement
  85         # ittf
  86         # backeach item in arr5
  87         # log 'item ', i, item
  88         # js
  89         # var i, i_len=arr5.length, item;
  90         # for (i= (i_len-1); i>-1; i--) {
  91         # item = arr5[i];
  92         # console.log('item ', i, item);
  93         # }
  94         #
  95     e break : statement
  96         # ittf
  97         # foreach item in arr5
  98         # ...
  99         # break
 100         #
 101     e continue : statement
 102         # ittf
 103         # foreach item in arr5
 104         # ...
 105         # continue
 106         #
 107     e label : statement
 108         # ittf
 109         # var i, j
 110         # label loop1
 111         # for i = 0; i < 3; i++
 112         # # The first for statement is labeled "loop1"
 113         # label loop2
 114         # for j = 0; j < 3; j++
 115         # # The second for statement is labeled "loop2"
 116         # if i === 1 && j === 1
 117         # continue loop1
 118         # log 'i = ' + i + ', j = ' + j
 119     e while : statement
 120         #
 121         # ittf
 122         # set parent = node.parent
 123         # while parent
 124         # set parent = parent.parent
 125         #
 126     e do : statement
 127         #
 128         # ittf
 129         # var result = ''
 130         # var i = 0
 131         # do i < 5
 132         # set i += 1
 133         # set result += i + ' '
 134         #
 135         # js
 136         # var result = '';
 137         # var i = 0;
 138         # do {
 139         # i += 1;
 140         # result += i + ' ';
 141         # } while (i < 5);
 142         #
 143     e switch : statement
 144         #
 145         # ittf
 146         # switch key
 147         # case 1
 148         # _ first()
 149         # case 2
 150         # _ second()
 151         # default
 152         # _ last()
 153         #
 154     e case : statement
 155         # ittf
 156         # see 'switch' element
 157     e default : statement
 158         # ittf
 159         # see 'switch' element
 160     e try : statement
 161         #
 162         # ittf
 163         # try
 164         # set num =/ 0
 165         # catch ex
 166         # log ex.message
 167         # finally
 168         # _ reset()
 169         #
 170     e catch : statement
 171         # ittf
 172         # see 'try' element
 173     e finally : statement
 174         # ittf
 175         # see 'try' element
 176     e throw : statement
 177         # ittf
 178         # see 'try' element
 179     e delete : statement
 180         # ittf
 181         # delete myvar

/src/ittf/lib/wizzi/schemas/js.wfschema.ittf

                        


   1 wfschema js
   2     # A schema modeling a javascript module.
   3     export-to json
   4     e statement
   5         # The base element for all code nodes, and
   6         # a generic code statement that will be emitted as is.
   7         # The indentation will depend to the node depth.
   8         # Inside an html tag means a text node without line feed.
   9         tag +
  10         r statement/s
  11     e comment : statement
  12         tag #
  13     e commentmultiline : statement
  14         tag ##
  15     e module : statement
  16         # The root element of the js schema.
  17         is-root

  19             default jsfile
  20             restrict
  21                 enum jsfile
  22                 enum nodejs.bin
  23                 enum react
  24                 enum es6
  25         a ecma
  26             default es5
  27             restrict
  28                 enum es5
  29                 enum es6
  30         a no_strict
  31             type boolean
  32             default false
  33         r feature/s
  34         m wzinitialize
  35             if this.kind === 'react' || this.kind === 'es6'
  36                 set this.ecma = 'es6'
  37             # referenced in wizzi-codegen.js.es6.module
  38             # > decl hasClasses = model.wzModelState.hasClasses
  39             # The 'hasClasses' is set in the 'wzInitialize' method
  40             # of the 'class' element.
  41             # log 'wizzi-js.model.module', this.wzName
  42             set this.wzModelState = ctx.modelState = {}
  43         m hasFeature
  44             param name
  45             foreach f in this.features
  46                 if f.wzName === name
  47                     return true
  48             return false
  49     e feature
  50         # A known feature that this module require. The list of available features
  51         # is enumerated in the restrict element of the 'kind' attribute.
  52         # Most features are autodetected during schema initialization.
  53         a kind
  54             restrict
  55                 enum argument-check
  56     e statementmultiline : statement
  57         # Inside an html tag means a text node preceded by a line feed
  58         tag ++
  59     $include common/parameters
  60     $include common/restrict
  61     $include js/vars
  62     $include js/expressions
  63     $include js/statements
  64     $include js/calls
  65     $include js/objects
  66     $include js/functions
  67     $include js/classes
  68     $include js/template
  69     $include js/react
  70     $include js/html
  71     $include js/wz
  72     $include js/graphql
  73     $include js/debug
  74     $include js/test
  75     declare
  76         function isDescendentOf
  77             param model
  78             param ancestor
  79             if !model.wzParent
  80                 return false
  81             if model.wzParent.wzElement == ancestor
  82                 return true
  83             return
  84                 _ isDescendentOf
  85                     @ model.wzParent
  86                     @ ancestor

                    

                

                

                    

                        
/src/ittf/lib/errors.js.ittf

                        


   1 module
   2     kind jsfile
   3     var md
   4         set module.exports
   5             {
   6     error( Node,  message,  node )
   7         var msg
   8             [
   9                 @ message
  10         if node
  11             if node.wzSourceLineInfo
  12                 var info = node.wzSourceLineInfo
  13                 var filePath = 'TODO'
  14                 if node.wzSourceFilepath
  15                     set filePath = node.wzSourceFilepath(info.sourceKey)
  16                 _ msg.push((' at row: ' + info.row))
  17                 _ msg.push((', col: ' + info.col))
  18                 _ msg.push((', source: ' + info.sourceKey))
  19                 _ msg.push((', in file: ' + filePath))
  20             elif node.row
  21                 _ msg.push((' at row: ' + node.row))
  22                 _ msg.push((', col: ' + node.col))
  23         set this.message = msg.join('')
  24         # log 'NodeError', this.message
  25         # set this.node = node

   2     $params name, value
   3     _ expect(${name}).to.be.a('number')
   4     _ expect(${name}).to.be(${value})

/src/t/checked_call_return_set.js.ittf

                        


   1 $group
   2     $params varName
   3     set ${varName}
   4         $hook
   5     if ${varName} && ${varName}.__is_error
   6         return ${varName}

                    

                

                

                    

                        
/src/t/checked_call_return.js.ittf

                        


   1 $group
   2     $params varName
   3     var ${varName}
   4         $hook
   5     if ${varName} && ${varName}.__is_error
   6         return ${varName}

                    

                

                

                    

                        
/src/t/checked_call.js.ittf

                        


   1 $group
   2     $params varName, message|@@null
   3     var ${varName}
   4         $hook
   5     if ${varName} && ${varName}.__is_error
   6         log '__is_error ${message}', ${varName}
   7         return callback(${varName})

                    

                

                

                    

                        
/src/t/error.js.ittf

                        


   1 $group
   2     $params name, arg1|@@null, arg2|@@null, arg3|@@null, arg4|@@null
   3     function ${name}Error
   4         $if arg1 != null
   5             param ${arg1}
   6         $if arg2 != null
   7             param ${arg2}
   8         $if arg3 != null
   9             param ${arg3}
  10         $if arg4 != null
  11             param ${arg4}
  12         set this.name = '${name}Error'
  13         $hook
  14         # 5/8/17 set this.stack = (new Error()).stack
  15     set ${name}Error.prototype.toString
  16         function
  17             return this.message
  18     set ${name}Error.prototype = Object.create(Error.prototype)
  19     set ${name}Error.prototype.constructor = ${name}Error
  20     set md.${name}Error = ${name}Error
  21     +

   2     $params result|notUsed
   3     function
   4         param err
   5         param ${result}
   6         $hook

                    

                

                

                    

                        
/src/t/f_cb_test.js.ittf

                        


   1 $group
   2     $params result|notUsed
   3     function
   4         param err
   5         param ${result}
   6         if err
   7             log 'err', err
   8             throw new Error(err.message)
   9         $hook

                    

                

                

                    

                        
/src/t/f_cb.js.ittf

                        


   1 $group
   2     $params result|notUsed
   3     function
   4         param err
   5         param ${result}
   6         if err
   7             return
   8                 _ callback
   9                     @ err
  10         $hook

/src/t/r_cb.js.ittf

   2     $params value|null
   3     _ callback
   4         @ null
   5         @ ${value}

                    

                

                

                    

                        
/src/t/repeater_increment.js.ittf

                        


   1 $group
   2     $params name
   3     _ process.nextTick
   4         function
   5             _ repeater_${name}(index_${name} + 1)

                    

                

                

                    

                        
/src/t/repeater.js.ittf

                        


   1 $group
   2     $params name, items, from|0
   3     var len_${name} = ${items}.length
   4     function repeater_${name}
   5         param index_${name}
   6         if index_${name} === len_${name}
   7             return
   8                 _ next_${name}
   9         var item_${name} = ${items}[index_${name}]
  10         $hook
  11     _ repeater_${name}(${from})
  12     function next_${name}
  13         $hook next

                    

                

                

                    

                        
/src/generate.wfjob.ittf

                        


   1 wfjob wizzi-js
   2     $
   3         var ittf_meta_folder    = path.join(__dirname, 'ittf', 'meta');
   4         var ittf_lib            = path.join(__dirname, 'ittf', 'lib');
   5         var ittf_examples       = path.join(__dirname, 'ittf', 'examples');
   6         var ittf_root_folder    = path.join(__dirname, 'ittf', 'root');
   7         var ittf_tests          = path.join(__dirname, 'ittf', 'tests');
   8         var dest_folder         = path.join(__dirname, '..', 'dist');
   9     model meta
  10         schema json
  11         src ${ittf_meta_folder}/index.json.ittf
  12     line ittf-lib
  13         cwd-folder ${ittf_lib}
  14         dest-folder ${dest_folder}/lib
  15         wfjob/any_js()
  16             ignore ${ittf_lib}/**/*__copy/**/*.js.ittf
  17         artifact any_ittf_inside___copy
  18             src ${ittf_lib}/**/*__copy/**/*.ittf
  19             extension ittf
  20     line ittf-examples
  21         cwd-folder ${ittf_examples}
  22         dest-folder ${dest_folder}/examples
  23         wfjob/any_js()
  24             ignore ${ittf_examples}/**/*__copy/**/*.js.ittf
  25         artifact any_ittf_inside___copy
  26             src ${ittf_examples}/**/*__copy/**/*.ittf
  27             extension ittf
  28     $include wfjob/root
  29     line ittf-tests
  30         cwd-folder ${ittf_tests}
  31         dest-folder ${dest_folder}/tests
  32         wfjob/any_js()
  33             ignore ${ittf_tests}/**/*__copy/**/*.js.ittf
  34         artifact any_ittf_inside___copy
  35             src ${ittf_tests}/**/*__copy/**/*.ittf
  36             extension ittf
  37         $include wfjob/any_tests_ittf
  38         $include wfjob/any_expected
  39     production
  40         dest-folder ${dest_folder}
  41         line-ref ittf-lib
  42         line-ref ittf-examples
  43         line-ref ittf-root
  44         line-ref ittf-tests
